# scatter-drop web — local dev fork config (copy to .env.local)
#
# scripts/dev-fork.sh prints a ready-to-paste block of these NEXT_PUBLIC_*
# values at the end of its run: the addresses come from
# contracts/deployments/<chainId>.json, while the chain id and RPC URL come
# from the script's own fork settings.

# Fork chain id + RPC (dev-fork re-labels the Sepolia fork to 31337 @ :8545 so
# it's distinct from real Sepolia — M1).
NEXT_PUBLIC_CHAIN_ID=31337
NEXT_PUBLIC_RPC_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8545

# (Retired) The balance-holder snapshot service (/api/snapshot/*) was removed
# with the ONCHAIN_SNAPSHOT source — a claim-window balance is gameable by
# moving funds between wallets. ALCHEMY_RPC_URL / SEPOLIA_RPC_URL (its archive
# RPC) are no longer read. The Tokamak staking snapshot lives on separately in
# StakingImport (a stake can't be un-staked quickly).

# Optional shared-secret gate for the operator data routes (/api/dune). When
# set, callers must send `Authorization: Bearer <secret>`. Unset = open (dev;
# rate-limited). Read by lib/server/apiAuth (name is legacy — it predates the
# snapshot removal but still guards the Dune import route).
# SNAPSHOT_API_SECRET=

# Deployment addresses. Either paste these (from dev-fork.sh), OR — simpler —
# copy the generated json so the app reads it at runtime without a rebuild:
#   cp contracts/deployments/31337.json apps/web/public/deployment.json
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DROP_FACTORY=0x...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FEE_TOKEN=0x...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AIRDROP_TOKEN=0x...
# NEXT_PUBLIC_TREASURY=0x...

# Block the DropFactory was deployed at. Optional but recommended for a real
# deployment: the campaign list scans DropCreated logs from here instead of a
# look-back window, so add it when building the deploy environment. On the local
# anvil fork it can be omitted — the app floors the scan at the fork block to
# avoid the rate-limited upstream provider.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_DEPLOY_BLOCK=

# --- IPFS pinning (optional) ---
# SERVER-ONLY Pinata JWT (no NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix — it must never reach the
# browser bundle). When set, published proofs.json files are pinned to IPFS
# and the wizard/manage console offer the on-chain CID anchor; unset = the DB
# store alone (local dev default). Read only by the /api/proofs* route handlers.
# PINATA_JWT=
# Public gateway used to read pinned proofs.json back (default https://ipfs.io).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_IPFS_GATEWAY=

# --- Native quests: Discord (docs/SOCIAL-TASK-DESIGN.md) ---
# SERVER-ONLY. OAuth app (identify scope) for wallet↔Discord binding, plus the
# platform bot token for membership/role verification. Create both at
# https://discord.com/developers/applications — the bot must be invited to the
# operator's server (no privileged intents needed for the members REST
# endpoint used here). Unset = Discord linking/verification answers 503
# (never a silent degrade). Never commit real values.
# DISCORD_CLIENT_ID=
# DISCORD_CLIENT_SECRET=
# DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN=

# --- Multi-network registry (Prisma + SQLite) ---
# Prisma reads DATABASE_URL from apps/web/.env (create it): DATABASE_URL="file:./dev.db"
# Setup: pnpm --filter @scatter-drop/web exec prisma db push && node prisma/seed.mjs
# SESSION_SECRET: ≥32-char secret for the SIWE admin session cookie (falls back to a dev value).
# SESSION_SECRET=change-me-to-a-random-32+char-secret
